LOCATION:SIDNEY AND LOIS ESKENAZI MUSEUM OF ART
GEO:39.169144;-86.519739
SUMMARY:Exhibition Closing Celebration for Mulyana: Vital Ecosystems
DESCRIPTION:This unique event invites visitors of all ages to experience 
 the exhibition through sound\, storytelling\, and hands-on creativity.Eve
 nt Schedule2ŌĆō2:30 p.m. | Musical PerformanceFirst-floor gallery  Immers
 e yourself in Wave Decay\, a live performance by a special string quartet
  featuring music composed by Timothy Reinholz. Inspired by oceanic proces
 ses and environmental data\, the piece echoes the rhythms\, erosion\, and
  resonance of the sea within Mulyana's underwater-inspired installation.3
 ŌĆō4 p.m. | Artist Talk &amp\; demoMartin Commons  Composer Timothy Reinh
 olz will share insights into his creative practice\, exploring how climat
 e and environmental data inform his work and how complex ecological issue
 s can be translated into powerful musical experiences.Throughout the Afte
 rnoonLight refreshments  Craft activities for all ages\, inspired by the 
 exhibition's themes of marine life\, care\, and interconnected ecosystems
     Come reflect\, create\, listen\, and celebrate &#160\;Mulyana: Vital 
 Ecosystems\, closing on June 28th.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  This unique event invites visitors of a
 ll ages to experience the exhibition through sound\, storytelling\, and h
 ands-on creativity.</p><p><strong>Event Schedule</strong></p><p><strong>2
 ŌĆō2:30 p.m. | Musical Performance</strong><br /><em>First-floor gallery<
 /em><br />  Immerse yourself in <em>Wave Decay</em>\, a live performance 
 by a special string quartet featuring music composed by Timothy Reinholz.
  Inspired by oceanic processes and environmental data\, the piece echoes 
 the rhythms\, erosion\, and resonance of the sea within Mulyana's underwa
 ter-inspired installation.</p><p><strong>3ŌĆō4 p.m. | Artist Talk &amp\; 
 demo</strong><br /><em>Martin Commons</em><br />  Composer Timothy Reinho
 lz will share insights into his creative practice\, exploring how climate
  and environmental data inform his work and how complex ecological issues
  can be translated into powerful musical experiences.</p><p><strong>Throu
 ghout the Afternoon</strong></p><ul><li>Light refreshments  </li><li>Craf
 t activities for all ages\, inspired by the exhibition's themes of marine
  life\, care\, and interconnected ecosystems  </li></ul><p>  Come reflect
 \, create\, listen\, and celebrate &#160\;<em>Mulyana: Vital Ecosystems\,
 </em> closing on June 28th.</p>
UID:20260621T180000Z-2287042@events.iu.edu
DTSTAMP:20260504T145801Z
