BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:IU Eskenazi School of Art, Architecture + Design
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260801
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260802
LOCATION:WYLIE HOUSE (307 E. SECOND STREET)
GEO:39.161697;-86.5309
SUMMARY:Louisa's Garden | Exhibition
DESCRIPTION:Louisa's Garden\, the Wylie House Museum's latest exhibition\
 , explores the way the eldest daughter of an IU professor was brave\, com
 plex\, and is still cherished today. For Louisa's Garden\, Graduate Curat
 orship student Maddie Guy selected five ensembles from the Elizabeth Sage
  Historic Costume Collection. These five nineteenth century ensembles\, t
 hough not directly related to Louisa Wylie Boisen (1839ŌĆō1930)\, were ca
 refully chosen to represent aspects of her life including Education\, Mot
 herhood\, Travel\, Religion\, and Gardening.Wylie House hours: FridayŌĆōS
 aturday\, 10amŌĆō4pm. Free\, guided tours begin on the hour every hour\, 
 with the last one beginning at 3pm. The museum is closed on major holiday
 s\, IU commencement weekend\, and during Indiana University breaks. Pleas
 e contact the museum to arrange group tours with more than eight people. 
  For more information about The Sage Collection\, please visit their webp
 age. (https://eskenazi.indiana.edu/about/centers-collections/sage-collect
 ion/index.html)  For more information about Wylie House Museum (https://l
 ibraries.indiana.edu/wylie-house-museum) visit their website.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p class="p1"><em>Louisa's Garden\,</em> the
  Wylie House Museum's latest exhibition\, explores the way the eldest dau
 ghter of an IU professor was brave\, complex\, and is still cherished tod
 ay. For <em>Louisa's Garden</em>\, Graduate Curatorship student Maddie Gu
 y selected five ensembles from the Elizabeth Sage Historic Costume Collec
 tion. These five nineteenth century ensembles\, though not directly relat
 ed to Louisa Wylie Boisen (1839ŌĆō1930)\, were carefully chosen to repres
 ent aspects of her life including Education\, Motherhood\, Travel\, Relig
 ion\, and Gardening.</p><p class="p1"><strong>Wylie House hours:</strong>
  FridayŌĆōSaturday\, 10amŌĆō4pm. Free\, guided tours begin on the hour ev
 ery hour\, with the last one beginning at 3pm. The museum is closed on ma
 jor holidays\, IU commencement weekend\, and during Indiana University br
 eaks. Please contact the museum to arrange group tours with more than eig
 ht people.</p><p class="p1">  For more information about The Sage Collect
 ion\, please visit their <a href="https://eskenazi.indiana.edu/about/cent
 ers-collections/sage-collection/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener
 ">webpage.</a></p><p class="p1">  For more information about <a class="ex
 ternal" href="https://libraries.indiana.edu/wylie-house-museum" target="_
 blank" rel="noopener">Wylie House Museum</a> visit their website.</p>
